JWT Authentication in Microservices using API Gateway: 

What actually happens when you securely call an API in a microservices architecture?

Here’s a simplified flow of JWT authentication using an API Gateway:

🔐 User logs in → Identity Server validates credentials
🎟️ JWT token is generated and it is issued to the client
🌐 Client sends API request with JWT
🚪 API Gateway validates the token from Identity server
🔄 Request is routed to respective microservices

✅ No session storage (stateless)
✅ Centralized security at gateway
✅ Scalable for microservices

This pattern is widely used in modern cloud architectures to ensure secure and efficient communication between services.
